summary: Bill Fanter provides a comprehensive weekly watchlist for November 17th, highlighting Nvidia earnings as the major market catalyst while warning against playing earnings with options due to IV crush. He reviews specific trade levels on major stocks including a successful Apple call trade that returned 300-400%, emphasizes the importance of staying in winning trades longer, and identifies key support/resistance levels across SPY, QQQ, and mega-cap tech stocks while noting decreasing volume heading into year-end.
